data.title: James Webb Space Telescope Coverage
data.meta_description: All assets associated with the tag: James Webb Space Telescope
data.text:
James Webb telescope catches glimpse of possible first-ever 'dark stars'

A team of astrophysicists analyzed images from the James Webb Space Telescope and found three bright objects that might be "dark stars," which are theoretical objects much bigger and brighter than our sun.

Five space telescopes combine to deliver dazzling galactic views

NASA's Chandra X-ray Observatory and James Webb Space Telescope combined to provide views like never before along with data from NASA's Hubble Space Telescope, the Spitzer Space Telescope, and the European Space Agency's XMM-Newton (X-ray)

Tony Rice, NASA Ambassador

Webb telescope spies proof of hidden planets

Astronomers used the James Webb Space Telescope to observe the first asteroid belt seen outside of our solar system and unveiled some cosmic surprises along the way.

Exoplanet is confirmed by new James Webb Space Telescope

The James Webb Space Telescope can add another cosmic accomplishment to its list: The space observatory has been used to confirm the existence of an exoplanet for the first time.

Developments in tech, energy, even work provide reasons for optimism in 2023

As 2022 comes to an end amid stubborn inflation, a "tripledemic," a climate crisis and a brutal war with no end in sight, it can be difficult to remember that good things happened this year, too.

A look at the 'Pillars of Creation'

New images from the James Webb Telescope provide a fresh look at the "Pillars of Creation." (NASA)

Even scientists didn't expect Webb telescope images of Jupiter to be this good

Rainbow auroras, giant storms and far-off galaxies are all on display in the latest images of Jupiter from NASA's James Webb Space Telescope.

By Madeline Holcombe, CNN

New Webb telescope image reveals the chaotic Cartwheel galaxy

The James Webb Space Telescope has peered through cosmic dust to reveal new details and a stunning image of a rare type of galaxy.

By Ashley Strickland, CNN

Granville County students inspired by images from telescope with local link

Students and others gathered at James Webb High School in Granville County for the reveal of new deep space images taken by a telescope named for the same man.

Granville County students part of world event watching deep space images from Webb telescope

The latest Webb Telescope images were revealed to groups watching on video screens from around world like in India, Israel, Canada and in the town of Oxford, North Carolina. Students and others gathered to watch NASA's latest "reveal" with 4 spectacular new pictures from the Webb Telescope.

Rick Armstrong, WRAL photojournalist

Who was James Webb, anyway?

In 2002, Sean O'Keefe, then the NASA administrator, announced that the agency's next telescope would be named for James Webb, who led NASA during the 1960s, when it was gearing up to land people on the moon. He was a staunch champion of space science.

Dennis Overbye, New York Times

A new space odyssey: Most powerful telescope delivers images of great beyond

A stellar nursery where stars are born, interactions between galaxies and a unique view of an exoplanet are just some of the new cosmic images are being shared Tuesday.

NASA releases images from James Webb telescope

We are seeing some of the deepest images of the universe ever recorded, images taken by the James Webb Space Telescope, named after a North Carolina man.

NASA reveals Webb telescope's new images of stars, galaxies and an exoplanet

A stellar nursery where stars are born, interactions between galaxies and a unique view of an exoplanet are just some of the new cosmic images are being shared Tuesday.

By Ashley Strickland, CNN

NASA to unveil new space telescope images today - here's a preview

The first glimpse of how the James Webb Space Telescope will change the way people see the universe has arrived. The rest of the high-resolution color images will make their debut today. Here are the details.

NASA releases first image from James Webb Space Telescope, more to come Tuesday

NASA will release the James Webb Space Telescope's first images on Tuesday. The 5 targets include nebulae, an exoplanet, and galaxies including one you might recognize from a holiday movie.

Tony Rice, NASA Ambassador

NASA shares teaser for Webb telescope's first image release

Get ready to see some awe-inspiring views of the universe as we've never seen it before.

By Ashley Strickland, CNN

James Webb Telescope's journey is nearly complete

After 28 days and 885,000 miles, the journey of the James Webb Space Telescope will reach its destination on Monday after controllers fire its thrusters, placing it a huge orbit around L2, a gravitationally stable point a million miles from Earth.

Tony Rice, NASA Ambassador
